  <datafield tag="545" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Boardman family of Dixon, Ill., including brothers John D. Boardman who served in Batteries F and I, 1st Illinois Artillery, during the Civil War, and William H. Boardman, 1868 graduate of the University of Michigan.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Letters of John and William Boardman to their father, John's letters describe his military experiences in Georgis, Tennessee, and Mississippi, including descriptions of fighting around Atlanta during the summer of 1864. William's letters describe his experiences as a freshman, including examinations, freshman-sophomore rivalry, and money problems. The collection also includes a few pages of William's accounts.</subfield>
